{
  "stem": "4113.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And for example, I would be roughed up sometimes outside.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember one episode in winter I went home.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They waited for me outside, threw me into the snow, rubbed me up was snow, my face was all swollen.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my mother went to the teacher to talk to him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "His name was Grouchka-- a fine gentleman.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I must say the teachers were wonderful, absolutely wonderful.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he grabbed that kid who did that to me, and he called him out in class and bawled the heck out of him, telling him his father used to work for a Jewish company.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a rubber, huge plant called Wudeta-- stood for Wurzel, Daar, Tarnow-- because they were the owners from the city of Tarnow.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he told him, you eat Jewish bread, for God's sake, and this is what you did to him?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He bawled the heck out of him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So all for example to tell you quite frankly, I sometimes don't like to tell those stories, because some of my Polish friends, you know, don't like when I talk that way.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But what I'm saying is the truth.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If I had to go to the washroom, I went home to go to the washroom rather than go to the washroom when all the other kids.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Or I would ask for permission during the lecture to go, so that no other kids were there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because they would turn around occasionally, and they would pee on me, you see?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I-- I either ran home, or I went-- or I went during the hour of schooling to the washroom.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So you know, but I guess you learn to live with these things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And you survive.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Did your father give you advice about how to deal with such incidences?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not really.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
